"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765677","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-11","<p>The government does not hold the relevant figures. However, we have done some analysis of the impact across all pension schemes and produced a factsheet on the subject, a copy of which I will place in the Libraries of the House.</p><p>There is no statutory requirement for pensions earned before 1997 to be increased once in payment. To require schemes now to pay increases to pre-1997 pensions would place an additional and unexpected burden on schemes and their sponsoring employers.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-10-11T16:41:55.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765677/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765677/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765677/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Digital Equipment: Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Work and Pensions of 17 January 2017, Official Report, column 279WH, what assessment he has made of the cost of index-linking pension rights acquired before 1997 for members of the Digital Equipment Ltd pension scheme.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","105966"
