"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765706","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-20","<p>The issue of the CPVO and their commissioning was discussed with the Commission on 26 September. Future arrangements for plant variety testing will be subject to negotiation with the EU.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-10-20T09:17:33.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765706/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765706/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765706/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-06","Community Plant Variety Office: National Institute of Agricultural Botany","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what talks he has had with the EU Commission to ensure that the Community Plant Variety Office continues commissioning variety testing contracts to the National Institute of Agricultural Botany after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","106328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765707","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-10-16","<p>The provision of on-site bookmakers at racecourses is a commercial matter for the racing and betting industries. Racegoers have access to a variety of betting options at the racecourse including fixed odds betting provided by on-course bookmakers at the side of the track, pool betting provided at the racecourse and online betting via smartphones.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-10-16T16:30:26.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765707/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765707/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765707/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-06","Bookmakers: Competition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment her Department has made of the effect on competition of the decision by Betfred to close on-site bookmakers at UK racecourses.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","106037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765708","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not hold this information. Childcare vouchers provided by employers are normally exempt from tax, therefore, employers are not required to report details to HMRC unless they provide more than the exempt amount to their employees.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","105844 ; 106407 ; 106408","2017-10-16T12:56:53.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765708/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765708/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765708/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Child Care Vouchers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people are in receipt of childcare vouchers in England.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","106406"
