"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765711","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-12","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions has responsibility for Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) and Jobseekers Allowance (JSA) claims in England, Scotland and Wales only. The Department for Communities in Northern Ireland has responsibility for ESA and JSA claims in Northern Ireland, and as this is a devolved matter we do not hold this information.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","105804","2017-10-12T14:19:05.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765711/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765711/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765711/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Employment and Support Allowance: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time taken is to process new claims for employment and support allowance in Northern Ireland in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","105800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765712","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>The average time taken to process joint tax claims, from the first point of receipt to the first day of payment, in the last 12 months was 30.31 days. The data is inclusive of both UK and International Claims.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have a public target of processing claims and changes for tax credits and Child Benefit customers within an average of 22 days for UK customers and 92 days for International customers. Both targets are currently being achieved.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-16T15:00:05.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765712/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765712/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765712/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average time taken is to process joint claims for tax credit from the day of application to the day of payment in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","105801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765713","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>HM Revenue and Customs regularly track the overall processing times for new Child Benefit claims. However, the processing times for those claims received specifically from Northern Ireland are not readily available and cannot be provided without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-16T16:05:38.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765713/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765713/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765713/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Child Benefit: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average time taken is to process child benefit claims from the day of application to the day of payment in Northern Ireland in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","105802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765714","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-12","<p>The average processing time for Jobseekers Allowance (JSA) claim decision to be made is 7.8 working days. This data is based on the last 12 months from October 16 – September 17.</p><p>The data provided relates to claims processed in England, Scotland and Wales.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-10-12T16:42:41.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765714/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765714/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765714/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Jobseeker's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time taken is to process new claims for jobseeker's allowance across the UK in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Emma Little Pengelly","Belfast South","Emma Little Pengelly","105803"
