"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765937","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-16","<p>In November 2015 the Government committed £150m for Transport for the North (TfN) to deliver multi-modal smart ticketing across the North of England.</p><p>TfN are preparing a business case for the programme, which will set out its scope and plan for rollout, costs and benefits and the necessary arrangements with passenger transport operators.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","106281 ; 106282 ; 106283 ; 106284 ; 106285","2017-10-16T16:14:19.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765937/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765937/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765937/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-06","Public Transport: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of proposals for smart ticketing for public transport in the North on the number of station staff employed in that region.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","106279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765938","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-16","<p>My Department is currently in negotiations with train operators as part of the smart ticketing programme, and I expect these negotiations to conclude by the end of November. The agreements reached, alongside collaborative working with Scotland, Transport for London and Transport for the North, will see the delivery of smartcard acceptance across the whole franchised rail network by the end of 2018, using a common standard, and building on previous government investment in rail industry smart ticketing systems.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-10-16T15:22:12.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765938/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765938/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765938/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-06","Public Transport: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to guarantee interoperability between smart ticketing systems for public transport provided by different franchise operators.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","106280"
