"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765947","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-12","<p>We will publish responses to the call for views alongside the Government response. I would like to assure the hon. Member that we are continuing to work with industry and enforcement partners to build a coordinated response to the growth of illicit streaming.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-10-12T14:22:59.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765947/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765947/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765947/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765947/answer/previousversion/13866","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Digital Technology: Television","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for the publication of the responses to the call for views by the Intellectual Property Office on IPTV set-top boxes.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","106175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765948","Department of Health","false","2017-10-16","<p>Following a detailed public consultation that ran from December 2015 to March 2016, the Government set out in its response to that consultation in February 2017 that it intended to amend the existing Charging Regulations. Over the course of the consultation and decision-making process the Government carefully considered the impact the changes may have on public health and on vulnerable groups.</p><p> </p><p>The amendment regulations maintain the existing exemptions in place for the purposes of protecting the public’s health and do not change our position of ensuring that the most vulnerable have access to free healthcare. The requirement for upfront charging will not apply in the case of treatment that clinicians consider immediately necessary, or otherwise urgent (such that it cannot wait until the overseas visitor can reasonably be expected to return home). This means that chargeable overseas visitors will never have immediately necessary treatment (which includes all maternity treatment), or urgent treatment withheld or delayed pending payment.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","106403","2017-10-16T15:46:05.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765948/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765948/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-06","Health Services: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the National Health Service (Charges to Overseas Visitors) (Amendment) Regulations 2017 on public health.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","105932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765949","Home Office","false","2017-10-18","<p>The Home Office has not placed any requirements on the NHS to report on patients’ immigration status.</p><p> </p><p>As specified in the Immigration Rules, the Home Office may refuse an immigration application where the applicant has failed to pay an NHS debt of £500 or more in accordance with the relevant NHS regulations on charges to overseas visitors. The Department of Health has put in place arrangements through which the NHS notifies the Home Office of these debts.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-18T14:20:44.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765949/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765949/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765949/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Immigration: Patients","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what requirements she has placed on the NHS to report on patients' immigration status.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","105896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765950","Home Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave to the Hon. Member for Linlithgow and East Falkirk on the 17th of June, UIN 1040</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-16T14:43:03.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765950/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765950/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765950/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to extend the Immigration Skills charge to EU citizens when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","106290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765951","Department of Health","false","2017-10-16","<p>Following a detailed public consultation that ran from December 2015 to March 2016, the Government set out in its response to that consultation in February 2017 that it intended to amend the existing Charging Regulations. Over the course of the consultation and decision-making process the Government carefully considered the impact the changes may have on public health and on vulnerable groups.</p><p> </p><p>The amendment regulations maintain the existing exemptions in place for the purposes of protecting the public’s health and do not change our position of ensuring that the most vulnerable have access to free healthcare. The requirement for upfront charging will not apply in the case of treatment that clinicians consider immediately necessary, or otherwise urgent (such that it cannot wait until the overseas visitor can reasonably be expected to return home). This means that chargeable overseas visitors will never have immediately necessary treatment (which includes all maternity treatment), or urgent treatment withheld or delayed pending payment.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","105932","2017-10-16T15:46:05.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765951/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765951/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765951/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-06","Health Services: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of up-front charges for healthcare on people not seeking early medical help due to their immigration status or the cost of healthcare.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","106403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765952","Home Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>The process of obtaining medical information is not a mandatory part of the asylum process nor is it a new process. Before any decision is made on an asylum claim it is vital we are aware of any information that is relevant to the award of any form of leave.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-16T15:06:52.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765952/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765952/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765952/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Asylum: Medical Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reason her Department has started contacting asylum seekers asking them to sign a consent form that would give her Department access to their personal medical records.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Davey","Kingston and Surbiton","Sir Edward Davey","106402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765953","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>The introduction of Minimum Unit Pricing in England and Wales remains under review. The Government awaits the outcome of the Scotch Whisky Association's decision to appeal the decision of the Scottish Courts and the impact of the implementation of this policy in Scotland.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-10-16T12:11:33.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765953/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765953/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765953/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Alcoholic Drinks: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to introduce minimum unit pricing for alcohol sales to reduce the effects of cheap alcohol on public health and crime levels.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765954","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>The administration of the tax system, including where appropriate the repayment of tax or duties, is a matter for HM Revenue and Customs. It would not be appropriate for Ministers to comment on the affairs of specific taxpayers.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-16T15:59:46.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765954/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765954/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765954/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether HM Revenue and Customs has the discretion to reimburse the Roadchef Employee Benefits Trust's fund; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765955","Home Office","false","2017-11-15","<p>As a matter of long standing policy and practice, the UK will neither confirm nor deny whether an extradition request has been made or received until such time as a person is arrested in relation to the request.</p><p>Between 2010 – 2016, 22 people were arrested in relation to extradition requests from the UAE to the UK. In the same period, 1 individual was extradited from the UK to the UAE, with the remaining cases discharged by the courts or still pending.</p><p>In regards to the cost to the public purse for legal aid for such requests, the Legal Aid Agency and Scottish Legal Aid Board does not collect data in the form requested.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-15T10:57:58.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765955/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765955/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765955/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-06","Extradition: United Arab Emirates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, (a) how many extradition requests have been made, (b) how many of those have been refused and (c) what the cost to the public purse for legal aid is for such requests made by the UAE in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765956","Scotland Office","false","2017-10-13","<p>I have regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) and Scottish Government ministers on a range of issues.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has legislation in place which requires manufacturers to place only safe products on the market and to take action where a safety issue is identified. BEIS is in regular contact with white goods manufacturers and AMDEA (the Association of Manufacturers of Domestic Appliances) and established a Working Group on Product Recalls and Safety to further improve the safety of white goods and the recalls system. The group made its final recommendations in July of this year and actions are underway to implement a number of their recommendations:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/report-to-margot-james" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/report-to-margot-james</a></p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-10-13T10:46:18.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765956/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765956/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765956/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-10-06","Tumble Dryers: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with (a) the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and (b) Scottish Government on tackling problems with tumble dryer safety in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765957","Department for Transport","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government currently has no plans to lower the drink drive limit. Our approach in tackling drink driving is through rigorous enforcement, tough penalties, and changing the social acceptability of drink driving.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-10-16T13:33:31.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765957/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765957/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765957/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-10-06","Driving under Influence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to reduce the drink-drive limit to 50mg.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765958","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>The UK is proud to remain the second largest international funder of the HIV response. The UK Government’s recent investment in the Global Fund to fight AIDS, TB and Malaria will provide anti-retroviral therapy for 1.3 million people living with HIV. The UK is also at the forefront of work to prevent further spread of AIDS, which remains a top killer of adolescents in Africa.</p><p>The STOPAIDS report highlights how DFID has responded to the changing epidemic by adapting its spend on HIV, noting also our assessment of how to maximise results by focussing on women and girls, key populations, together with the integration of HIV responses into the wider health system and broader development priorities.</p><p>We will continue to lead the way by working with civil society partners, international governments and organisations, to ensure the ambitious international commitments on HIV are met, saving even more lives and ending AIDS as a public health threat by 2030.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T13:59:42.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765958/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765958/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765958/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","HIV Infection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the implications for her Department's policies of the report by STOPAIDS entitled A Stocktake Review of DFID's Work on HIV and AIDS, published in September 2017.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765959","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-13","<p>DFID’s assessment of progress on integrating the HIV response and reducing incidence is drawn from reports and data produced by UNAIDS and other partners including the World Health Organisation and the Global Fund to fight AIDS TB and Malaria. Progress towards integration into wider health programmes is also informed through reviews, which are publicly available on the DFID Development Tracker, carried out by DFID in-country health advisers.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-10-13T13:56:20.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765959/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765959/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765959/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-06","HIV Infection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how her Department monitors and assesses the effectiveness of HIV and AIDS awareness campaigns and training as part of their integration into wider health programmes funded by her Department; and how her Department measures reducing the incidence of HIV and AIDS.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765960","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-16","<p>Protecting consumers from unsafe, faulty and counterfeit goods is a priority. I set up the Working Group on Product Recalls and Safety in October 2016 to bring together product safety experts, the fire service and trading standards professionals to identify necessary improvements to the system of product recalls and safety. The Group published its report in July setting out recommendations and outlining the actions the Working Group has been taking. This includes working with the British Standards Institution (BSI) to develop a code of practice on corrective action and recalls. The Government will respond in the autumn.</p><p>The Department funds National Trading Standards (NTS) who prioritise national and cross-local authority boundary consumer enforcement in England and Wales. A successful programme of operations to tackle the sale of counterfeit and unsafe goods being made available on social media is ongoing. Similarly Trading Standards Scotland coordinates and enforces cross boundary and national casework also undertaking specialist functions which includes tackling e-crime.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-16T12:55:23.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765960/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765960/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765960/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Electronic Equipment: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps have been taken since the Westminster Hall debate on faulty electrical imports in March 2016 to review consumer protection against internet sales of faulty or counterfeit mobile telephone chargers, tablets and similar goods.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765961","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-16","<p>Product safety is a priority of this Government and the UK has legislation in place, which requires manufacturers to place only safe products on the market and to take action where a safety issue is identified.</p><p>It is our priority to continue the UK’s strong history of protecting consumers. The European Union (Withdrawal) Bill will convert directly applicable EU law into UK law and provide a power to correct parts of the law that no longer work. This will help maximise certainty for consumers and businesses as we leave the EU.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-16T12:51:05.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765961/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765961/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765961/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Electronic Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his policy is on (a) regulating the import of electrical goods such as mobile phone chargers and (b) consumer protection and redress with trading partners for faulty of sub-standard goods after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","106095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765962","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-11","<p>The Government has no plans to remove the longstanding arrangements for managing transmission constraints, under which various types of generation are compensated in order to change their planned output.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-11T13:28:35.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765962/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765962/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765962/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans his Department has to remove the process of constraint payments whereby wind turbine operators are recompensed at times of surplus generation and attempted stabilisation of the grid.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","106308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765963","Department for Education","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) collects and publishes data on students enrolled at UK Higher Education Institutions. Statistics on numbers of students with disabilities are published as part of the Statistical First Release on higher education student enrolments and qualifications obtained at higher education providers, which can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications" target="_blank">https://www.hesa.ac.uk/news/12-01-2017/sfr242-student-enrolments-and-qualifications</a>.</p><p>Statistics for the 2016/17 academic year will be available from HESA in January 2018.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-10-16T12:05:54.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765963/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765963/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765963/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-06","Students: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many full-time disabled students were registered on higher education courses in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","106239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765964","Department of Health","false","2017-10-11","<p>It is the Government's policy that clinical commissioning groups should have regard to the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline on the assessment and treatment of people with fertility problems when commissioning services for which they are responsible. This includes the recommendation in the guideline that three cycles of in vitro fertilisation be offered to qualifying couples where the woman is under the age of 40 and one cycle where the woman is between the ages of 40 and 42.</p><p> </p><p>The NICE guideline is evidence based best practice for clinicians but is not mandatory. The availability of National Health Service funded fertility treatment is and always has been a matter for local determination. Decisions on the level of service provision are underpinned by clinical insight and knowledge of local healthcare needs and priorities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-10-11T13:17:42.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765964/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765964/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765964/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-06","In Vitro Fertilisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the level of geographical variation of IVF funding; and whether it is his Department's policy that clinical commissioning groups implement NICE recommendations to commission funding for three cycles of IVF.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","106243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765965","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-11","<p>Government commissioned WSP/Parsons Brinckerhoff to review the available evidence on the human response to Amplitude Modulation (AM) noise produced by wind turbines. The final report of the review was published on 25 October 2016<strong> [1].</strong></p><p>We encourage Local Authorities and developers to apply the recommendations of the report as appropriate when considering planning applications for new sites to protect local residents from excessive AM noise.</p><p>To date, no evidence has been brought to the Department’s attention that changes the recommendations of the report.</p><p> </p><p><em><strong>[1]</strong></em><em> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/review-of-the-evidence-on-the-response-to-amplitude-modulation-from-wind-turbines" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/review-of-the-evidence-on-the-response-to-amplitude-modulation-from-wind-turbines</a></em></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-10-11T16:17:34.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765965/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765965/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765965/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Wind Power: Health Hazards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the Oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy of 12 September 2017, Official Report, column 635, if he will provide an update on the Government's monitoring of the effect on human health of wind turbine low-frequency sound and infrasound; and what assessment his Department has made of those findings.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","106244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765966","Department for Education","false","2017-10-16","<p>The repayment threshold for pre-2012 undergraduate loans has been increased annually in line with RPI since April 2012, and this will continue.</p><p> </p><p>The repayment threshold is currently £17,775, and will rise to £18,330 from 6 April 2018.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-10-16T11:52:19.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765966/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765966/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765966/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-06","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what her policy is on raising the threshold for repayment of student loans for graduates who started their course before 2012.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765967","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-17","<p>The Government is requiring local authorities where persistent exeedances of nitrogen dioxide concentrations have been identified to produce local air quality plans to reduce the pollution in the fastest possible time. We are helping them by providing £255 million to develop and implement their plans. In addition we will be establishing a Clean Air Fund, which will allow local authorities to bid for additional money to support the implementation of measures to improve air quality. This funding is over and above the £2.7 billion we are already investing to support air quality improvements.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-17T16:33:50.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765967/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765967/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765967/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-06","Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much funding has been allocated from the public purse to local authorities to support steps to establish air quality plans.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765968","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-13","<p>Sheffield City Council has been identified in the UK plan for tackling roadside nitrogen dioxide concentrations as a local authority with concentrations of nitrogen dioxide (NO<sub>2</sub>) projected to be persistently in exceedance of the legal limit. It is required to produce a local air quality plan to reduce levels of NO<sub>2</sub> in the shortest possible time. Sheffield City Council has therefore been allocated initial funding to develop a proposal for a feasibility study. Further funding will be made available to carry out that feasibility study and for the implementation of agreed measures to bring Sheffield into compliance with the legal limit in the shortest possible time.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-13T14:41:00.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765968/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765968/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765968/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-06","Air Pollution: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether any funding has been allocated from the public purse to support Sheffield Council in establishing its air quality plans.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765969","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-17","<p>Through the Air Quality Grant we help local authorities tackle air quality in their areas in order to reduce the impact on peoples’ health and create cleaner and healthier environments. This fund has awarded more than £52 million to a variety of projects since it started in 1997, including schools engagement work by local authorities.</p><p>During air pollution episodes, Defra issues advice via the UK Air website which includes links to health advice issued by Public Health England (PHE).</p><p>My officials are currently working with PHE and the Association of Directors of Public Health to develop a series of outreach events aimed at Directors of Public Health and designed to help them deliver and communicate local action.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-17T16:30:00.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765969/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765969/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765969/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-06","Air Pollution: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what guidance his Department plans to provide to schools in areas of high air pollution hotspots to help them protect children's health.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765970","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-11","<p>I refer the honourable member back to the answer provided by the Parliamentary Under-Secretary for the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, Margot James, on 31 October 2016; and to the answer provided by the former Chief Secretary to the Treasury, David Gauke, on 22 September 2015.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-10-11T11:29:09.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765970/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765970/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765970/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Minimum Wage: Arrears","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of arrears identified by national minimum wage investigations in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17 have been subsequently repaid to workers to whom they are owed.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765971","Women and Equalities","false","2017-10-11","<p>Government Equalities Office (GEO) officials have examined a number of advertisements and notices constituting alleged race or nationality discrimination which the hon. Member has brought to the Government’s attention.</p><p> </p><p>The GEO has forwarded this material to the Equality and Human Rights Commission, which has powers to enforce the Equality Act 2010 in cases where it suspects that unlawful discrimination may have occurred.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-10-11T15:39:01.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765971/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765971/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765971/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-10-06","Migrant Workers: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, pursuant to the Answer of 9 September 2017 to Question 6824, when the Government Equalities Office next plans to update her on reports of discrimination against non-UK EU nationals seeking employment.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","105981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765972","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-11","<p>Copies of the written submissions submitted to the Review will be published on the Gov.uk website in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-11T16:30:46.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765972/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765972/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765972/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will place in the Library copies of written evidence submitted to the Taylor review of modern working practices published on 11 July 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765973","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-11","<p>Officials in the Department met a number of business organisations and businesses, trade unions and worker representative groups, academics and third sector organisations in the course of the Review. They also met officials from other Government Departments. We are unable to quantify how meetings were held in total.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-11T16:18:02.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765973/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765973/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765973/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many meetings were held by officials of his Department on the Taylor review of modern working practices between 30 November 2016 and 11 July 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765974","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-11","<p>The total calculable cost of the Review was £73,724.45. This figure includes the cost of the Review Chair’s time, travel expenses for the Chair and expert panel members, costs of regional events and the cost of design and printing the report.</p><p>In addition to the costs set out above, a number of Government policy officials, lawyers and analysts from a number of Government departments worked on this Review and these costs were met from existing departmental budgets.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-11T13:24:33.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765974/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765974/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765974/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the cost to the public purse was of the Taylor review of modern working practices.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","106376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765975","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>Credit unions play a key role in offering affordable, responsible credit to underserved communities. The Government has supported the sector in the following ways:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Announcing at Autumn Statement 2016 that a greater proportion of funds recovered from illegal money lenders will be allocated to incentivise vulnerable people to join, save and borrow with a credit union instead of turning to loan sharks;</p></li><li><p>Increasing the maximum interest rate that credit unions can charge on loans from 2% to 3%. This has helped credit unions become more stable and allowed them to offer reliable, affordable credit to consumers who may otherwise have had to resort to more expensive means;</p></li><li><p>Contributing £600,000 to an initiative developed by the Archbishop of Canterbury and Young Enterprise, to start savings clubs in primary schools and educate young children in the benefits of saving, while promoting awareness of credit unions to children and their parents. Lifesavers works with local credit unions to help run savings clubs in schools; and</p></li><li><p>Initiating the Credit Union Expansion Project, a £38 million project aimed at helping the sector modernise and offer new services.</p></li></ul>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-10-16T11:05:05.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765975/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765975/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765975/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on the promotion of credit unions as an alternative to pay day lenders.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765976","HM Treasury","false","2017-10-16","<p>In March, the government launched the Childcare Choices website which brings together information about all the different help with childcare offered by the government – including Tax-Free Childcare. Since then, the Childcare Choices website has had more than one million unique users, and more than 700,000 people have completed the site’s Childcare Calculator to find out which government support best suits their circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC and DfE have worked together on a communications and engagement programme, including national, regional and social media, and communications through industry stakeholders. Parents who have signed up for ‘Keep Me Updated’ email updates on the new schemes are also being notified by direct email when they become eligible. HMRC officials have also attended promotional events across the UK with childcare providers, local authorities, parent groups and other childcare industry stakeholders.</p><p> </p><p>DfE and HMT ministers have undertaken visits to nurseries to promote Tax-Free Childcare, including one in East Renfrewshire where they spoke to them about their experiences of the scheme.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-10-16T15:42:37.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765976/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765976/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765976/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-10-06","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how the Government is promoting the uptake of the tax-free childcare scheme to workers and parents in (a) the UK and (b) East Renfrewshire.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765977","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-10-16","<p>On 12 October my noble friend the Parliamentary Under Secretary of State, Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth, met Angela Constance MSP (Cabinet Secretary for Communities, Social Security and Equalities in the Scottish Government) together with Carl Sargeant AM (Cabinet Secretary for Communities and Children in the Welsh Government) in Edinburgh. The meeting was the second in a series aimed at exploring common interest and sharing best practice on community cohesion. Among the topics for discussion was a presentation by Interfaith Scotland.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-10-16T16:05:53.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765977/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765977/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765977/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-10-06","Race Relations: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what joint working the Government is undertaking with the Scottish Government to promote racial tolerance and interfaith dialogue.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","106206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765978","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-16","<p>The Government recognises the important role post offices play in communities across the county, especially for the Post Office’s more vulnerable and elderly customers.</p><p> </p><p>With over 11,600 post offices in the UK, the Post Office network is at its most stable in decades due to the significant investment that has been made to maintain and protect it. This investment has delivered the fresher customer environments, increased opening hours and greater efficiency needed to succeed in Post Office’s competitive and changing markets.</p><p> </p><p>Post Offices are offering nearly a million extra opening hours every month and there are more than 4,400 branches open on Sunday, making Post Office the country’s largest Sunday retail network. Nearly 93% of the UK population live within one mile of their nearest post office, and over 99% within three miles.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-16T15:34:37.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765978/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765978/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765978/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Post Offices: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of the closure of post office counter services on vulnerable older customers; and what alternatives are available to those customers.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765979","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-12","<p>As of 22 September 2017 there were 5,162 employers signed up to Disability Confident nationally. This total includes 76 employers registered in the Glasgow West District, which takes in East Renfrewshire constituency. Information is not collected at Parliamentary Constituency level.</p><p>An up-to-date list of Disability Confident employers can be viewed or downloaded from gov.uk: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disability-confident-employers-that-have-signed-up" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disability-confident-employers-that-have-signed-up</a></p><p>Efforts to promote Disability Confident to employers are being led by The Disability Confident Business Leaders Group, which comprises prominent national businesses and industrial and professional membership bodies. The Group encourage and support other employers to sign up.</p><p>Disability Confident is also promoted to employers via a wide range of Government activities including press releases, social media, events, conferences and links to the Gov.Uk site.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-10-12T13:23:58.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765979/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765979/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765979/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Learning Disability: East Renfrewshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how (a) many employers in East Renfrewshire signed up to the Disability Confident Scheme and (b) that scheme is promoted to employers.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765980","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-13","<p>The information requested on the number of individuals eligible to receive Pension Credit by parliamentary constituency is not available at that level.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of February 2017, there were 2,021 individuals in receipt of Pension Credit in East Renfrewshire.</p><p> </p><p>This information is published and available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p> </p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2017-10-13T12:04:24.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765980/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765980/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765980/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Pension Credit: East Renfrewshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many East Renfrewshire residents (a) are eligible to receive and (b) claim pension credit.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765981","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-16","<p>The location and provision of individual post offices is the operational responsibility of Post Office Limited; the company manages that and oversees the network.</p><p> </p><p>Departmental officials meet regularly with Post Office Limited to discuss a wide range of matters affecting the network, and this will include its provision of post offices across the country.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-16T15:19:04.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765981/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765981/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Post Offices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when officials of his Department last met representatives of the Post Office to discuss the provision of local post offices.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765982","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-16","<p>The provision of individual post offices is the operational responsibility of Post Office Limited; the company that manages and oversees the UK’s post office network.</p><p> </p><p>I understand that there are currently 10 open post offices in the Honourable Member’s constituency, 9 of which have been transformed under the Post Office’s modernisation programme, offering an additional 224 opening hours per week, with 6 branches open on a Sunday.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-16T15:22:16.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765982/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765982/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765982/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-06","Post Offices: East Renfrewshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what his policy is on the retention of local post office services in East Renfrewshire.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","105871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765983","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-16","<p>Her Majesty’s Government continues to engage with the Government of Bangladesh over what is, in our view, discriminatory action against a British company. Guidance was issued in December 2013 to assist compliance with the World Health Organisation’s Frame​work Convention on Tobacco Control and we have observed the guidelines for support to the tobacco industry at all times.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-10-16T15:44:53.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765983/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765983/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-06","Bangladesh: British American Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government has given assistance to British American Tobacco in its challenge to the claim for unpaid VAT brought against it by the Government of Bangladesh; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","105750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765984","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-10-12","<p>The Secretary of State for Justice has had no discussions with the Law Commission about including a review of the UK’s corporate laws in their 13<sup>th</sup> programme of Law Reform.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-10-12T10:34:59.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765984/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765984/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765984/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-10-06","Commercial Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions he has had with the Law Commission on including a review of whether the UK's corporate laws are fit for purpose in its 13th programme of law reform.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","106310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765985","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-10-12","<p>The Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union visited Northern Ireland in September 2016 meeting with the then Northern Ireland Executive and stakeholders including NI Screen and SONI (System Operator for Northern Ireland). He also visited Dublin last September for his first overseas visit following his appointment as Secretary of State. He has not visited the border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland, however I have visited Northern Ireland twice since joining the Department as Parliamentary Under Secretary of State and accompanied the Secretary of State on his Dublin visit. During my most recent trip in September 2017 I visited the border and met with Re-Gen waste, a cross-border waste management company and InterTradeIreland, which offers practical support to cross-border businesses.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-10-12T14:48:05.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765985/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765985/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765985/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-06","Department for Exiting the European Union: Northern Ireland and Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many times he has visited (a) Northern Ireland and (b) the border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland since his appointment as Secretary of State.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","106149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765986","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-10-12","<p>For the Child Support Agency (CSA), Page 7 of the Client Funds Account publication provides figures on the CSA Arrears deemed uncollectable. The publication can be accessed at this link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/578767/hc855-client-funds-account-2015-16-1993-and-2003-cms.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/578767/hc855-client-funds-account-2015-16-1993-and-2003-cms.pdf</a></p><p>Information on geographical breakdowns on the Client Funds Account is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-10-12T16:29:23.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765986/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765986/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/765986/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-10-06","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what percentage of Child Support Agency Arrears are deemed uncollectable in (a) Aberdeen City (b) Aberdeenshire and (c) Scotland.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","106321"
